D210 Representation and Reporting Course Description

Representation and Reporting focuses on communicating observations and patterns to diverse stakeholders, a key aspect of the data analytics life cycle.
This course helps students gain communication and storytelling skills. It also covers data visualizations, audio representations, and interactive dashboards using Tableau. 

COURSE OBJECTIVES

- Storytelling with Data
The graduate communicates data insights to technical and nontechnical audiences.

- Data Visualizations and Representations
The graduate creates data representations to offer insight into an organizational problem.

- Tableau Dashboards
The graduate designs interactive Tableau dashboards to support executive decision-making. 
